ectOutputStream)`\n- `BCECPrivateKey.readObject(ObjectInputStream)`\n\nHowever, the dynamic-access report still cannot mark these call sites as covered because the tracked frames are:\n\n- `org.bouncycastle.jcajce.provider.asymmetric.ec.BCECPrivateKey.readObject(Unknown Source)`\n- `org.bouncycastle.jcajce.provider.asymmetric.ec.BCECPrivateKey.writeObject(Unknown Source)`\n\nThe `bcprov-jdk15on:1.48` class file for `BCECPrivateKey` does not contain line number information for these private serialization methods. The report implementation only marks dynamic-access call sites as covered when the native-image tracked frame has a concrete source line that matches JaCoCo line coverage. Since the frame line is `null`, these call sites remain reported as uncovered even though the methods are executed.\n\nI did not add another test because any additional public API serialization path still resolves to the same private `readObject`/`writeObject` methods and the same `Unknown Source` tracked frames. Covering them in the report would require changing harness/reporting behavior or replacing/shadowing the library class with line-numbered bytecode, which is outside the allowed scope and would violate the test rules.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02223dfb0f282903016a10c367a438819dbf5396d3caa854b9\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3037, "output": 811, "cacheRead": 52224, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 56072, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779483484213, "responseId": "resp_02223dfb0f282903016a10c35d4274819d992efb04db6dc124"}, "toolResults": []}
